    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="687"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.6711/6–1845</note>
                <head>No. 687 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Director of Near Eastern and African Affairs</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_HLW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Henderson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d687fn1">This memorandum bears the following manuscript
                        notation by <persName corresp="#p_MHF1">Matthews</persName>: “There was no
                        mention of <persName corresp="#p_T1">Turkey</persName>’s ‘integrity’ at
                        Yalta. HFM[.]”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-22">June 22,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Office Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>In handing the attached reply<note n="2" xml:id="d687fn2">
                        <ref target="#d688">Document No. 688</ref>.</note> to a representative of
                    the British Embassy, you may wish to indicate verbally that the officers of the
                    Department present at the Yalta conversation concerned do not recall <persName
                        corresp="#p_SMIV2">Marshal Stalin</persName> as having taken at that time,
                    with regard to <persName corresp="#p_T1">Turkey</persName>’s independence and
                        <hi rend="italic">integrity</hi>, a position so definite as that indicated
                    by the British Government in its <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> of June
                        18.<note n="3" xml:id="d687fn3">Attachment to <ref target="#d683">document
                            No. 683</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HLW1">L[<hi rend="smallcaps">oy</hi>] W H[<hi
                                rend="smallcaps">enderson</hi>)</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
